I came for a event called Badass Ladies of Rock and really enjoyed myself. The bartender was really nice and happy to help my partner choose their drink, and the space was cozy without being too cramped. The location was really convenient for me because I live within walking distance. I don't drive if I know I am going to drink, and I was able to walk home after a couple of drinks without any issue. Also the bathroom was clean and I was very appreciative of that since most clubs and bars I've been to have disgusting bathrooms.

Really liked this place! Door guy was super helpful and recommended a restaurant(their kitchen was closed, show night). Will call for tickets was easy. Reentry was no problem. Stage was elevated so there are no bad seats. Low table, high table, sit, stand...could see from anywhere.  Sound was very good. Everything was both loud and clear.  People were really enjoying themselves on the dance floor. Probably the most welcoming dance floor I've ever seen. Really positive crowd.  Good beer list. Great bar service! And there's a game room downstairs with a pool table.  Great show venue, great bar!

We were very pleasantly surprised by this really cool venue. Its comfortable and intimate, yet spacious with a great space to dance. There's even a downstairs which is a nice chill out area to play pool. We attended the club for the very first "Afterlife" goth night. The place was bustling and booming with goths dancing and socializing to the best and new goth/darkwave music I've heard in a long time. The dancefloor was always alive with excitement as the happy hum of folks chatting happily made this night the best time I've had in years. Reminds me of the Red Party night in New York.  Definitely will return to the next one!

My husband and I went to Thunder Road on New Year's Eve for dinner and to see Playin' Dead.  The music was great and the venue was perfect. I was especially impressed with the service. The chef, the bartenders,  and everyone else working there seamlessly provided the crowd with food and drinks all night. Thanks, Thunder Road, for a wonderful night.

My girlfriend and I were visiting Boston for the first time and someone recommended we check out some live music at Thunder Road. We decided to head there and check it out the Bearly Dead, who plays there every Wednesday evening.  It was a great open venue with plenty of room to move around and not feel crowded. The Bearly Dead were fantastic and the crowd consisted of a lot of friendly patrons.  We didn't end up trying any food, but it smelled and looked great.  I'd highly recommend stopping by if you get the chance.

What a nice addition to Union Square. Great modern bar with awesome sound. Saw Bearly Dead there on Wednesday. The sound in the room definitely rivaled Church. Good beer selection, nice service from the bartenders and the folks working the door. I liked that there are USB plugs at the outlets along the bar to recharge. Didn't try the food yet, but it looks like they have some nice seating areas elevated enough so you can see the stage while sitting at your table. For just $5 for the Monday Akashic Record residency and the Wednesday Bearly Dead residency, I'll be coming here frequently.

Stumbled onto this new rock club and bistro in Union Square in the place that used to be radio.  They completely re-did the inside, it's so much different and classy, and they added a real stage and PA!  Really neat burger menu with music inspired burgers like The Led Zeppelin (sliders), The Rasta Burger (pineapple), the Jamband (bacon jam) and some other cool ones.  My friends and I saw a killer bluegrass band and had a great time.  Seeing as how live music joints in the city are dropping like flies, glad to see a new one.  Hope they do some great business.  I'll definitely be back.
